Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yoshino-chan, how are you? Are you feeling a little better?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Not just a little bit better, a lot better. Still feels a bit uncomfortable, but not a lot.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: That's good. It seems to have worked really well.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino has never seen such sorcery before. What art did Miyako cast?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: It's the art of transferring a person's pain and suffering to its user.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Eh...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Transfer to yourself? Not to get rid of it?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yes. This cannot relieve suffering from illness or physical injury, but possible if caused by special sorceries or magic.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Sorceries with special effects, that means...".

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Miyako, how is Yoshino?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I think she'll be fine now. We can continue with the mission.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Good...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Do tell us about your mission, why did you came back to this mountain, Miyako? Now that we've converged, I like you to brief us on the purpose of the mission.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: The Mist on this mountain has been cleared, hasn't it? But, the situation clearly changed after Miyako turned back. Why is that even after the source of the outbreak has been eliminated?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: We weren't able to get rid of the source. Or, in my opinion, a new source manifested.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I'm sure you all know what happened here?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Oui. Children who had gone missing all over M. Nishiki were all found here, all at once, no?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: We the SSS suspect perhaps something like a temporary Gate opened and brought the children here. It's part of our mission to find out.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: It is certain that the children were gathered here in some way. But I disagreed with the Railway Army's supposition that someone living in these mountains wanted to harm the children.

Name: Putra
Phrase: What makes you think that? One wrong move and they could all be dead, right?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: But as it turned out, they all survived. They didn't get hurt, they didn't get sick. They survived for many days in this labyrinth of torii gates.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: For days?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: The children were trapped here for a long time before the Railway Army came to their rescue. It's unusual to survive for this long inside such Phantom Mist.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: That being said, yes. It takes awhile for rescue teams to arrive after people went missing in various places, not immediately...

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Did the children have any resistance to Phantom Mist? People such as the Mistism cultists and Miss Karamachi were less susceptible to the Mist and less likely to be attacked by monsters.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: That's not true. The children were not resistant. The torii protected them.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Finally. Someone else thought the same thing like me.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino is from Nishiki. Yoshino understands at least this much.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: The temples and torii gates of Nishiki have the power to protect people from bad things. That is why many of them function as barriers to prevent Phantom Mist from occurring.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: In fact, this place where we are escaping from the Mist is also within the Torii's boundaries.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako is right. Even if bad things possess us, the blessing of Jushin-sama and the power of nature will repel them away.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: So this means another culprit brought the children here.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I believe so. That's why I didn't retreat and came back to this place. I came back to this place because I wanted to find out the truth.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: And just before we left the labyrinth, I sensed someone's presence. I couldn't determine whether it was a person or a demon. I couldn't tell for sure. I felt like they were asking for my help...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: It's just as Yoshino predicted - You turned back into the maze to see if there were any children left behind. No wonder M. Nishiki Railway Army said 'stragglers'.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Wouldn't it have been better to report back to your comrades and then plan a strategy? It's too dangerous to turn back alone. Why did you take such a risk?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: What do you mean...?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Just because I thought it was dangerous, doesn't mean I think it would be difficult?

Name: Putra
Phrase: I didn't expect that answer.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Isn't it normal? I didn't violate any orders.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: My mission is to protect the children who were found here at the Senbon Torii. It is not part of my orders to return to the base with them as the search party withdraws.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Besides, those who took part in the search party here were somewhat underpowered, both as sorcerers and as soldiers. I don't think they would have made it to this place anyway.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Miyako is surprisingly workaholic. I thought you're more like Versailles' straight man.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Well, alright. I see your point, Miyako.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: But you should also understand our emotions when we came to help you. Yoshino risked her life to save ya.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Understand emotions...

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Human emotions are so difficult...

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Hey Yoshino-chan, what did you feel on the way here?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yoshino felt like heart was going to burst. Yoshino was so worried about Miyako, that its very depressing.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: So... I made you feel anxious.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I'm so sorry. I didn't expect you all to come.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: There's no need to apologise. Miyako went back to help people. Yoshino and friends are here to help.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: That's right, isn't it? Shashou?
Of course, there was no way she could just leave here and return to base when there's still Mist. It will also be necessary to find out the identity of the presence that Miyako had sensed.

But Yakutsk is right, Yoshino's physical condition is our priority. If it was due to injury or illness, we could do something about it. But if this Senbon Torii is affecting her then I have to expect the worst to happen.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: There is nothing to worry about. I've found out the reason for Yoshino-chan's illness.
That helps. Nishikese sorcery is very foreign. It's reassuring to have a sorceress like Miyako watching over us.
So what's going on? Why on earth did Yoshino get so ill? She's in a worse condition than Vivienne, is this because of the many torii here?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Vivienne's symptoms are typical magic intoxication. I think she will get used to it in time.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: But Yoshino-chan's case is different. She's afflicted by a somewhat strong curse.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Strong curse?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yes, she's cursed.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Just to be clear, it is a curse in the sense that it converts emotions such as hatred and sadness into harm upon a person's body and soul.

Name: Putra
Phrase: I don't need you to explain that to me!

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Don't say it so non-chalantly. We have to do something about it, don't we?

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: That's true. If it's a curse, we have to break it.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I agree that we should move on to find a way to do that. Don't worry so much about Yoshino's curse. I absorbed most of hers, so she'll be fine.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: You absorbed...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Please don't tell me, that was the kind of sorcery you used earlier?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yes, it was. I transferred Yoshino-chan's curse to me. I have a strong resistance to curses, so I probably would be fine.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: How can there be no problem? Miyako can only endure so much. We have to find a way to break the curse properly.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: If it's not the Torii or the Phantom Mist, then there must be a sorcery maniputor. I'll find whoever it is and bring down justice.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Miyako has been investigating this mountain for a long time now, hasn't you? Have you ever sensed anyone suspicious or any other unpleasant presence?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: We fought a strong demon when we rescued the children, but it wasn't an enemy who used special sorceries or magic. Maybe there's something around the top of the mountain, but... I haven't found a way to get up there.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: So there's likely another maze from here onwards.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yes. It's quite complicated and I'm having trouble getting further. But I keep getting the feeling that someone is watching me. I think it's too early to turn back...

Name: Queensway
Phrase: About that, I've been thinking. The presence that Miyako felt when she retreated... Could it be that fox-faced girl we saw?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Fox?

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Yes. She is a Nishikese girl wearing a fox mask. We saw her on the way here. She showed us the way and... She doesn't look like she's from the living world.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: That girl knew Miyako's name. She probably saw Miyako here all the time.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I haven't seen any girl with a fox mask. Even if she wasn't living, I'd think I'd recognise her right away...

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: She might have been hiding inside the torii too. Yoshino thinks she was too shy to talk to Miyako alone. Yoshino understands that feeling very well.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I have no idea what's going on.

Name: Putra
Phrase: There she is! The floating fox!

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: How did she know we were inside the barrier?

Name: Fox Masked Girl
Phrase: Get out of the barrier now. You are going to the top of the mountain.

Name: Fox Masked Girl
Phrase: The only way to clear the Mist is to go to the top. Look for the black torii. Don't be distracted by the vermillion torii. You will find it if you look carefully.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: That's the fox girl? I've never seen her before.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: She said we should look for the black torii. Yoshino and friends haven't seen any of those.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I've been looking at these torii too, but I've never seen a black one.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: We can never be sure. There are so many torii gates. It wouldn't be surprising if we missed one or two.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: This is where... you know who, comes in conveniently.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Paddington Elrond! The legendary Divine Child with perfect rote memorization that never forgets what she once saw, and a bottomless stomach!

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: So Paddington, did you see any black gates on the way here?

Name: Paddington
Phrase: No! Not one!

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Useful. Thank you.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: ...That's what she said.

Name: Miyako
Phrase: I've never seen anyone call Miko-sama 'useful' before...

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Let's do as she says once we're there. It's thanks to her that we were able to meet up with you, Miyako.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Yes, that's right. Thanks to her that we may be able to move on now. Miyako, can you disenchant the barrier?

Name: Miyako
Phrase: Yes, I understand. Then we will return to the present torii.

Miyako used her spell again, and a door in the shape of a torii appeared in front of her. Outside the door, which emitted a strong light, is supposed to lead us back to the Senbon Torii, a series of vermillion torii gates...

Name: Miyako
Phrase: This is...
But the view that stretched outside the barrier was an eerie cave with walls lined with Nishikese dolls...
